<HL>
   Marketing Brief -- TVX Broadcast Group Inc.:
   Holders Advised to Accept
   Paramount's Latest Offer
</HL>
<DATE>
09/26/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B6
</SO>
<CO>
   PCI TVXGC
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
MEDIA, PUBLISHING, BROADCASTING, ELECTRONIC PUBLISHING (MED)
</IN>
<LP>
   Independent directors of TVX Broadcast Group Inc.
recommended that shareholders accept a sweetened offer by
Paramount Communications Inc. for the 17% of TVX shares in
public hands.
   New York-based Paramount, which owns 83% of the television
broadcaster, boosted its offer to $9.50 a share from $7.50
for more than seven million shares outstanding. The offer
would be valued at $66 million for the remaining shares of
the Virginia Beach, Va., company.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   In over-the-counter trading yesterday, TVX shares closed
at $9, up $1.375 a share. The offer is subject to negotiation
of an acquisition agreement and approval by TVX shareholders.
   Paramount is an entertainment and publishing concern.
</TEXT>
